# Environment Variables for Rasoi AI

# =============================================================================
# REQUIRED ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# Google Gemini AI API Key (REQUIRED)
# Get your API key from: https://aistudio.google.com/
# This is required for the AI-powered recipe generation feature
NEXT_PUBLIC_GEMINI_API_KEY=your_gemini_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# OPTIONAL ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# Node Environment
# Set to 'development' for local development, 'production' for deployment
NODE_ENV=development

# Next.js Configuration
# Uncomment and set if you need custom Next.js behavior
# NEXT_PUBLIC_APP_URL=http://localhost:3000

# =============================================================================
# DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# Enable/disable Next.js telemetry (optional)
# Set to 1 to disable telemetry collection
# NEXT_TELEMETRY_DISABLED=1

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# For Vercel deployment, these are typically set automatically:
# VERCEL_URL - Your deployment URL
# VERCEL_ENV - Deployment environment (development, preview, production)

# For other platforms, you may need to set:
# PORT=3000
# HOST=0.0.0.0

# =============================================================================
# FUTURE ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES
# =============================================================================

# These variables are not currently used but may be added in future versions:

# Database connection (if user accounts are added)
# DATABASE_URL=your_database_connection_string

# Authentication service (if user auth is added)
# AUTH_SECRET=your_auth_secret_key
# NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Email service (if notifications are added)
# EMAIL_SERVER=your_email_server
# EMAIL_FROM=noreply@rasoi-ai.com

# Analytics (if tracking is added)
# GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_ID=your_ga_id

# External APIs (if additional features are added)
# RECIPE_API_KEY=your_recipe_api_key
# NUTRITION_API_KEY=your_nutrition_api_key

# =============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# =============================================================================

# 1. Copy this file to .env.local in your project root:
#    cp .env.example .env.local

# 2. Replace 'your_gemini_api_key_here' with your actual Gemini API key

# 3. Uncomment and set any optional variables you need

# 4. Never commit .env.local to version control - it's already in .gitignore

# 5. For deployment, set environment variables in your hosting platform:
#    - Vercel: Project Settings > Environment Variables
#    - Netlify: Site Settings > Build & Deploy > Environment Variables
#    - Other platforms: Check their documentation for environment variable setup

# =============================================================================
# API KEY SETUP GUIDE
# =============================================================================

# To get your Google Gemini AI API Key:
# 1. Visit https://aistudio.google.com/
# 2. Sign in with your Google account
# 3. Click "Get API key" in the left sidebar
# 4. Click "Create API key" button
# 5. Select "Create API key in new project" or choose existing project
# 6. Copy the generated API key
# 7. Paste it in your .env.local file

# API Usage Notes:
# - Free tier has rate limits (15 requests per minute, 1500 per day)
# - Keep your API key secure and never commit it to version control
# - Monitor your usage at https://aistudio.google.com/
# - Consider implementing caching in production to reduce API calls